POLOKWANE – Celebrated worldwide in recognition of the contribution that fathers and father figures make in children’s lives, Father’s Day is a time to honour the special men in our lives and give recognition to the paternal bonds as well as the influence that fathers have in society. Being a father brings with it a set of responsibilities and the ages at which dad’s undertake the responsibility of fatherhood varies. The Polokwane Review spoke to fathers of varying ages to find out how they take on the responsibility of being a father. 